WHCommonDataModelImplementationGuide

The official URL for this implementation guide is: 

http://ibm.com/fhir/cdm/ImplementationGuide/wh.cdm.fhir

Watson Health Common Data Model Profiles

Quality Measure
resource.description: The quality measure profile is limited to measures with proportion and ratio scoring methods. The profile requires an initial population, denominator, and numerator in accordance with FHIR quality reporting guidelines. Measure population and measure population exclusions are not allowed.  The profile also supports care gap populations for additional use cases.

resource.description: The Hierarchical Condition Category (HCC) with the highest associated DCG prospective cost weight assigned to a person. This field is assigned during the DCG Build and  is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Identified Pronouns
resource.description: Gender, typically described in terms of masculinity and femininity, is a social construction that varies across different cultures and over time.  This value is often used for identity purposes and should be collected directly from the patient.

resource.name: Ingestion Batch Id
resource.description: Generated by an ingestion service such as the Health Record Ingestion (HRI) management API, the ingestion-batch-id represents a collection/grouping of messages that the producer submitted together.  The 'batch' definition needs to be agreed upon by data producers and data consumers.

resource.name: Language Rank

resource.name: Legally Documented Sex

resource.name: Likelihood of hospitalization
resource.description: The Likelihood of Hospitalization value assigned to an individual that predicts the likelihood of hospitalization or home care in the next 6 months for an individual, expressed on a scale of 100. This score is produced by the DxCG Likelihood of Hospitaliz

resource.description: Unique static identifier for the measure population that does not change between cohort engine runs. This is a user-friendly textual key (internal use only) that identifies a specific population. This id should be unique across all measures and should not change when a measure is versioned or when overrides are applied.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Blood Disorder
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to disorders of the blood (hematological). This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Cardiovascular Disorder
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to disorders of the heart and circulatory system (cardiovascular). This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Development Disability
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to developmental disabilities, such as intellect, attention deficit disorder, autism, and Down syndrome. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incur

resource.name: Percent Contribution Diabetes
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to diabetes. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Gastrointestinal Disorder
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to disorders involving the gastrointestinal system. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Hepatobiliary Disorder
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to disorders or diseases of the hepatobiliary (liver and bile) system and pancreas. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Infections
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to viral, bacterial and parasitic infections, including HIV. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Metabolic Disorder
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to nutritional disorders and disorders of the metabolic system. This category excludes diabetes. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred cate

resource.name: Percent Contribution Musculoskeletal Disorder
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to disorders of the musculoskeletal system and connective tissue. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Neonates
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to care relating to newborns. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Neoplasms
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to malignant and non-malignant cancers (neoplasms), including radiation and chemotherapy. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Neurological Disorder
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to disorders of the brain and nervous system. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Other Conditions
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to other conditions that are low frequency (such as organ transplants and amputations) or conditions that are low contributors to prospective risk (such as eye

resource.name: Percent Contribution Pregnancy
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to conditions related to pregnancy, prenatal through delivery. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Psychiatric Disorder
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to mental health diseases and disorders, including depression. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Respiratory Disorder
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to disorders of the respiratory system, including COPD and asthma. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Substance Abuse
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to conditions related to drug and alcohol abuse. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Percent Contribution Trauma and Adverse Effect
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to acute trauma injuries (including fractures, burns, head injuries, and traumatic amputations), complications of care, poisonings, and allergic reactions. Thi

resource.name: Percent Contribution Urinary System Disorder
resource.description: The percentage of condition-related DCG prospective risk for an individual that is attributable to disorders of the urinary system, including the kidneys. This category excludes diabetes. This percentage is available only within the DCG Incurred category.

resource.name: Process Client ID
resource.description: The client id as recorded by the data producer or data integrator.

resource.name: Process Name
resource.description: The name of the process or service that has produced the data held in the FHIR resource or element.

resource.name: Process Organization
resource.description: The organizing entity that owns the process that has produced the data held in the FHIR resource or element. For example if an IBM analytic service has been the producer, the process-organization value would be IBM.

resource.name: Process Record ID
resource.description: The record id that the data producer or data integrator uses internally to identify this data.

resource.name: Process Timestamp
resource.description: The timestamp the data was generated within this FHIR resource or element.

resource.name: Process Type
resource.description: The classification type of the process that has produced the data held in the FHIR resource or element. For example, if the process is primarily a Natural Language Processing (NLP) service, the type may be specified as NLP. Or if the process is primarily one that aggregates and groups related items, the type may be specified as Grouper.

resource.name: Process Version
resource.description: The version of the process or service that has produced the data held in the FHIR resource or element.

resource.name: Project Annual Cost
resource.description: The overall future projected annual resource expenditure for the individual, as assigned through the DCG methodology, based on diagnoses and drugs, and eligibility information during the DCG time period. This value indicates the projected allowed amount  to be incurred by the individual during a 12-month period subsequent to the DCG time period.

resource.name: RelatedIssue
resource.description: Related issues that can be combined to fulfill a single time period for a given care gap.

resource.name: RelatedObservation
resource.description: Related observations that can be combined to fulfill a single time period for a given care gap or other measure population.

resource.name: Risk Category Code
resource.description: The IBM Advantage Suite standard code for the risk category, using values of Risk Score Concurrent NonRescale. The risk category only applies to the Commercial All-encounter Medical and Drug models.

resource.name: Risk Score Nonrescale
resource.description: The Relative Risk Score assigned to an individual that indicates the expected relative cost risk of the individual compared to the average in the time period, expressed on a scale of 100. Because the score is not rescaled to the population on which the DCGs were assigned, the average (100) represents the average for the nationwide dataset on which the model was developed. This score is produced by the DCG models and is available only within the DCG Incurred category.
